OL,3,CNew laws to crack down on disruptive
OL,4,Cprotests come into force
OL,6,FThe new orders can impose a range of
OL,7,Frestraints including preventing people
OL,8,Ffrom being in a particular place or
OL,9,Farea, participating in disruptive
OL,10,Factivities and being with protest
OL,11,Fgroups at given times.
OL,13,FThey can also stop individuals from
OL,14,Fusing the internet to encourage
OL,15,Fprotest-related offences.
OL,17,FThese orders can be imposed on those
OL,18,Fwho have, on at least two occasions,
OL,19,Fcommitted protest-related offences,
OL,20,Ffor example locking-on, or breached
OL,21,Fthe conditions of an injunction.
