OL,3,CNew laws to crack down on disruptive
OL,4,Cprotests come into force
OL,6,FSerious Disruption Prevention Orders
OL,7,Fwere introduced as part of the Public
OL,8,FOrder Act 2023, which was passed last
OL,9,Fyear, and breaching an order will be a
OL,10,Fcriminal offence that will carry a
OL,11,Fmaximum penalty of six months in
OL,12,Fprison and/or an unlimited fine.
OL,14,FHome Secretary James Cleverly said:
OL,15,F"The public has a democratic right to
OL,16,Fprotest and this government will
OL,17,Falways uphold that.
