OL,3,CNew laws to crack down on disruptive
OL,4,Cprotests come into force
OL,6,F"Many of these laws are so broad and
OL,7,Fvague, including locking-on offences,
OL,8,Fthat when combined with these new
OL,9,Fmeasures, it could lead to people
OL,10,Fbeing banned from protesting entirely
OL,11,Fdue to something as simple as having
OL,12,Fpreviously linked arms with other
OL,13,Fprotesters.
OL,15,F"It's especially concerning that there
OL,16,Fare even more crackdowns on protests
OL,17,Fplanned in the Criminal Justice Bill,
OL,18,Fincluding proposed bans on face
OL,19,Fcoverings which would impact
OL,20,Fclinically vulnerable protesters and
OL,21,Fpolitical dissidents.
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@AOU
