OL,3,CNew laws to crack down on disruptive
OL,4,Cprotests come into force
OL,6,F"Protest is a human right, not a gift
OL,7,Ffrom the state. The government should
OL,8,Fbe supporting people's right to
OL,9,Fprotest, not chipping away at it."
OL,11,FThe Criminal Justice Bill will also
OL,12,Fprevent individuals from using the
OL,13,Fright to protest as a defence for
OL,14,Fcommitting criminal offences.
OL,16,FThe Home Office has said this string
OL,17,Fof measures will ensure that people
OL,18,Fcan exercise their democratic right to
OL,19,Fprotest while ensuring the public can
OL,20,Fgo about their daily lives safely and
OL,21,Fwithout serious disruption.
